\mathcal{L} = h^H(\hat{f} + e)(\hat{f} + e)^Hh + \lambda (e^H e - 1) 
\lambda \geq0
\mu = \max_{\|e\| \le 1} | \langle h, \hat{f}+e \rangle |= \max_{\|e\| \le 1} | \alpha+\langle h, e \rangle |
\alpha = \langle h, \hat{f}\rangle
\{\langle h, e \rangle \}_{\|e\| \le 1} =  \{z \in \mathbb{C} | |z| \le \|h\| \}
\max_{|z| \le \|h\|} |\alpha + z|
z = \frac{\alpha}{|\alpha|} \|h\|
\alpha \neq 0
z=\|h\|
\mu = |\alpha|+\|h\| = | \langle h, \hat{f}\rangle | + \|h\|
